    <h3>Vampirism</h3>
    <hr>
    <h4>Vampiric Stages</h4>
    <p>
        Vampirism can be either contracted after not dealing with sanguine vampiris or 
        it can be given by vampires if that is what the person wishes. Vampirism grows 
        in stages if the person does not feed after a certain amount of days. 
        These are the stages and the abilities that get aquired after each stage is achieved.
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Stages</th>
            <th>Elemental Passives</th>
            <th>Spells/Powers</th>
            <th>Abilities</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Stage 1</td>
            <td>
                Resist Frost: 20%<br>
                Weakness to Fire: 20%
            </td>
            <td>
                Vampiric Drain (spell version)
                Vampire's Servant<br>
                Vampire's Sight
            </td>
            <td>
                Nightwalker's Footsteps<br>
                Vampiric Strength: 5 pts<br>
                Weakness to Sunlight: 15 pts
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Stage 2</td>
            <td>
                Resist Frost: 30%<br>
                Weakness to Fire: 30%
            </td>
            <td>
                Vampiric Drain (spell version)
                Vampire's Servant<br>
                Vampire's Sight<br>
                Vampire's Seducation
            </td>
            <td>
                Nightwalker's Footsteps<br>
                Vampiric Strength: 10 pts<br>
                Weakness to Sunlight: 30 pts
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Stage 3</td>
            <td>
                Resist Frost: 40%<br>
                Weakness to Fire: 40%
            </td>
            <td>
                Vampiric Drain (spell version)
                Vampire's Servant<br>
                Vampire's Sight<br>
                Vampire's Seducation
            </td>
            <td>
                Nightwalker's Footsteps<br>
                Vampiric Strength: 15 pts<br>
                Weakness to Sunlight: 45 pts
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Stage 4</td>
            <td>
                Resist Frost: 50%<br>
                Weakness to Fire: 50%
            </td>
            <td>
                Vampiric Drain (spell version) 
                Vampire's Servant<br>
                Vampire's Sight<br>
                Vampire's Seducation<br>
                Embrace of Shadows
            </td>
            <td>
                Nightwalker's Footsteps<br>
                Vampiric Strength: 20 pts<br>
                Weakness to Sunlight: 60 pts
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <p>
        As well as having these buffs/debuffs; vampires also get complete immunity 
        to all poisons and diseases. The main thing you have to worry about as a vampire 
        is the Sun. Your Health, Mana, and Stamina do not regenerate while in sunlight, 
        your health is also reduced by the weakness to sunlight debuff in the table above.										
    </p>
    <br>
    <h4>Vampire Lord Form</h4>
    <p>
        If the person is gifted blood from a very powerful vampire lord, they also 
        get the ability to transform into a Vampire Lord themselves. Your entire form 
        changes as well as your form of combat. You are able to unlock perks that will 
        enhance your gameplay while in the form of a Vampire Lord. You get the ability to 
        unlock a perk once the session you unlock the ability to transform is complete(the amount 
        of perks you get is determined by the dm). Can only turn into a Vampire Lord once a day. 
        The table below this shows the default actions you can take in Vampire Lord form.
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Actions</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Melee Strike</td>
            <td>Basic swipe of your claw on a single target(damage based of Vampiric Strength stat)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Vampiric Drain</td>
            <td>Use your blood magic to abosrb 25 points of health from the target</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Vampire's Servant</td>
            <td>Reanimate a dead body to fight for you for 2 turns</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <br>
    <h4>Vampire Lord Perks</h4>
    <p>
        The table below shows all the perks you can unlock for Vampire Lord form.
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Perk Name</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Requirement</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Power of the Grave</td>
            <td>50 additional points of Health, Mana, and Stamina in Vampire Lord form</td>
            <td>None</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Detect all Creatures</td>
            <td>Detects all creatures in the area</td>
            <td>Power of the Grave</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Mist Form</td>
            <td>Turn into invulnerable mist(cant attack of be attacked) for 2 turns</td>
            <td>Detect all Creatures</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Blood Healing</td>
            <td>Killing a person with a power attack(melee) will restore all your Health</td>
            <td>Power of the Grave</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Poison Talons</td>
            <td>Melee Attacks deal 20 points of poison damage</td>
            <td>Blood Healing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Night Cloak</td>
            <td>Enemies in melee range are attacked by bats taking 8 points of damage per turn for 4 turns</td>
            <td>Poison Talons</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Vampiric Grip</td>
            <td>Can pull an enemy to you from a distance and deals 5 points of damage per turn once close</td>
            <td>Power of the Grave</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Summon Gargoyle</td>
            <td>Summons a Gargoyle to fight for you for 2 turns</td>
            <td>Vampiric Grip</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Corpse Curse</td>
            <td>Target that fails to resist is paralyzed for 2 turns</td>
            <td>Summon Gargoyle</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
