<div class="text-content w3-display-container">
    <h3>Lycnthropy</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>
        Lycanthropy can be aquired by being gifted another werewolf's blood. 
        This power grants the person complete immunity to disease as well as 
        the power to transform into a powerful werewolf. Can only turn 
        into a werewolf once a day.					
    </p>
    <br>
    <h4>Werewolf Form</h4>
    <p>
        As a werewolf you get powerful abilities that will have your opponents wishing 
        they had never faced you. You can get more abilities by unlocking perks 
        within the werewolf perk tree. You get the ability to unlock a perk once the session 
        you unlock the ability to transform is complete(the amount of perks you get is determined 
        by the dm). The table below shows off the defauly actions you can take in Werewolf form.										
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Actions</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Melee Strike</td>
            <td>Basic swipe of your claw dealing 25 damage on a single target(damage based off Bestial Strength stat)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Close Fling</td>
            <td>Flings a single target down nearby the user forcing them to get up for a turn</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Beastial Howl</td>
            <td>Preform a mostrous howl to scare any nearby enemies up to level 20 forcing them to flee for 1 turn</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <br>
    <h4>Werewolf Perks</h4>
    <p>
        The table below shows all the perks you can unlock for Werewolf form.
    </p>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Perk Name</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Requirement</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Bestial Strength(1-4)</td>
            <td>Do 25/50/75/100% more damage with melee strike in werewolf form</td>
            <td>None</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Totem of Ice Brothers</td>
            <td>Call fourth 2 Ice wolves to fight for you for 2 turns</td>
